node.title: NZ politician cycles to hospital, in labour, to give birth … again
node.alt: New Zealand MP Julie Anne Genter birth
node.description: New Zealand member of parliament Julie Anne Genter gets on her bicycle and heads to the hospital to give birth — again.
node.content: ["New Zealand MP Julie Anne Genter got on her bicycle early on Sunday and headed to the hospital.", "She was already in labour and she gave birth an hour later.", "\"Big news!\" the Greens politician posted on her Facebook.", "\"At 3.04am this morning we welcomed the newest member of our family.", "\"I genuinely wasn't planning to cycle in labour, but it did end up happening.", "\"My contractions weren't that bad when we left at 2am to go to the hospital \u2014 though they were 2-3 minutes\u00a0apart and picking up in intensity by the time we arrived 10 minutes later,\" Ms Genter wrote.", "A dual citizen, Ms Genter\u00a0was born in the US state of\u00a0Minnesota and before moving to New Zealand\u00a0in 2006.", "Ms Genter \u2014 her party's spokesperson for transport issues and whose Facebook profile includes \"I love my bicycle\" \u2014 also biked to the hospital in 2018 for a previous birth.\u00a0", "At the time, she said she rode to\u00a0Auckland City Hospital to give birth to her son because there \"wasn't enough room in the car\".", "Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern famously took maternity leave while in office and brought her three-month old to a United Nations\u00a0meeting because\u00a0she was still breastfeeding.", "Reuters"]
